OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FChancellor Rishi Sunak     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdefends wife Akshata Murty 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fin row over non-dom status 
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Rishi Sunak has defended his wife's tax
OL,6, affairs, calling reports on her        
OL,7, non-domicile status "unpleasant        
OL,8, smears".                               
OL,10,FAkshata Murty opted to claim non-dom   
OL,11,Fstatus, meaning she does not have to   
OL,12,Fpay UK tax on her overseas income.     
OL,14,FThe BBC estimates she would have       
OL,15,Favoided #2.1m a year in UK tax.        
OL,17,FThe non-dom scheme is legal but Labour 
OL,18,Fsays it would be "breathtaking         
OL,19,Fhypocrisy" if the chancellor's wife had
OL,20,Freduced her tax bill as he raised taxes
OL,21,Ffor millions of workers.               
